# My Journey with GDG Women of Wearables Pune

## How I Joined GDG WOW Pune

My journey with GDG WOW Pune began quite unexpectedly. I had been following tech communities in Pune for a while, but hadn't found one that truly resonated with my interests in emerging technologies like wearables and IoT. One evening while browsing through LinkedIn, I stumbled upon a post about an upcoming GDG WOW meetup focusing on wearable technology innovations. The diverse panel of speakers and the inclusive community approach immediately caught my attention.

What really convinced me to join was their emphasis on creating a supportive environment for everyone interested in technology, regardless of their background or experience level. I had been looking for a community where I could learn, contribute, and grow alongside like-minded individuals passionate about the future of technology. GDG WOW Pune seemed to offer exactly that.

I registered for their upcoming event the same day, filled with both excitement and a touch of nervousness about stepping into a new community. The registration process was straightforward, and I received a warm welcome email with all the details I needed, which already gave me a positive impression of how the community was organized.

## My First Day at the GDG WOW Event

The first GDG WOW event I attended exceeded all my expectations. It was held at a modern co-working space in Pune with excellent facilities. As soon as I walked in, I was greeted by friendly volunteers who helped me check in and gave me my name badge along with some cool GDG swag (the stickers immediately found their way to my laptop!).

The day began with a casual networking session over coffee. Despite being new to the community, several organizers approached me, introduced themselves, and made me feel welcome. They were genuinely interested in learning about my background and what brought me to the event. This initial interaction set a positive tone for the entire day.

The opening keynote was delivered by a leading woman in wearable technology, who shared insights about the future of health monitoring wearables and their potential impact on preventive healthcare. Her presentation was not only informative but also inspiring, demonstrating the real-world applications of the technology we were there to discuss.

What I particularly appreciated was the interactive format of the sessions. Rather than just listening to presentations, we participated in hands-on workshops where we got to experiment with wearable prototyping kits. I worked with a small group to conceptualize a fitness wearable for senior citizens, and the collaborative energy in the room was amazing. People freely shared ideas, helped each other troubleshoot, and provided constructive feedback.

During lunch, I had meaningful conversations with other attendees who came from diverse backgrounds - some were seasoned developers, others were students, and a few were even from non-technical fields but had an interest in wearable technology. This diversity of perspectives made the discussions incredibly rich and thought-provoking.

The afternoon sessions included lightning talks by community members showcasing their projects and experiences. I was inspired by how supportive the audience was, especially toward first-time speakers who were sharing their journey in technology. It created an atmosphere where everyone felt encouraged to participate and contribute.

By the end of the day, I had not only learned a great deal about wearable technology but had also connected with several people who shared my interests. The organizers concluded the event by announcing upcoming workshops and hackathons, and I immediately knew that I wanted to be part of this community going forward.

## Why GDG WOW Stands Out

What makes GDG WOW Pune special is their commitment to creating an inclusive tech community that focuses on knowledge sharing and practical application. They emphasize collaboration over competition and make a conscious effort to welcome newcomers.

The first event convinced me that I had found a tech community that aligned with my values and interests. Since then, I've been an active member, participating in workshops, contributing to community projects, and even mentoring new members who, like me, are taking their first steps into this wonderful community.

I'm grateful for the chance encounter that led me to GDG WOW Pune and excited about continuing this journey of learning and growth with such an amazing group of technology enthusiasts.

---

*Written by Harsh Kundargi, GDG WOW Pune Member*